1. A body of water, smaller than a river, contained within relatively narrow banks?
Crick.

2. What the thing you push around the grocery store/supermarket?
The bagboy.

3. A metal container to carry a meal in?
Can.

4. The thing that you cook bacon and eggs in?
Fry Daddy.

5. The piece of furniture that seats three people?
LOVEseat... *wink*

6. The device on the outside of the house that carries rain off the roof?
Peter with an umbrella.

7. The covered area outside a house where people sit in the evening?
Gazeeeeebo

8. Carbonated, sweetened, non-alcoholic beverages?
Coke.

9. A flat, round breakfast food served with syrup?
Hotcake

10. A long sandwich designed to be a whole meal in itself?
Reuben... No! Hoagies... Mmmm...

11. The piece of clothing worn by men at the beach?
Jeans.

12. Shoes worn for sports?
Sandals

13. Putting a room in order?
De-childizing

14. A flying insect that glows in the dark?
A flaming moth, which got too near the tiki torches...

15. The little insect arthropod that curls up into a ball?
Sowbug.

16. The children's playground equipment where one kid sits on one side and goes up while the other sits on the other side and goes down?
Totterteeter

17. How do you eat your pizza?
With my mouth.

18. What's it called when private citizens put up signs and sell their used stuff?
Moving.

19. What's the evening meal?
Supper.

20. The thing under a house where the furnace and perhaps a rec room are?
PeterS' Room.

21. That plant that kids throw at each other because it sticks to clothing?
Tumbleweeds.

22. Those little balls of froth on plants in spring, which contain some moth or other's eggs?
Bug-cum.

23. Girls' lower-half underwear?
Drawers.

24. Boys' lower-half underwear?
Skivies.

24. The cloth you had when you were little and always slept with, and perhaps sucked?
Pookie.

25. Warm knitted top typically made of wool?
Woolhat... DUH.

26. Baked in an oven, made of flour, butter, an egg, milk:
Chess Pie... If you add a few dozen more eggs.

27. A single thistledown seed flying free:
Wax Minute.

28. Place where you. Er. You know. Use the euphemism:
In the bushes.

29. The thing that you walk on that runs parallel to the street:
Yellow Line.

30. The sometimes grassy area in the middle of the street which separates both sides of the traffic:
Roadkill Cemetary.

31. What water comes out of?
*giggles* Welllll....

"The newspapers... Full of news."

"Not the real news, you know. They don't print the real news. That's nothing but censored press clippings from the state-run Department of Propaganda."

"All our news is controlled. You know who runs the Federal Reserve Board. Nobody does. Aliens from Planet X. That Alan Greenspan even looks like a Klingon. A lot of people don't believe in aliens, but I know they exist. I saw one. At the 7-11. It was getting a large Slurpee with sprinkles. It's all part of the conspiracy. Newspapers, aliens, the Kennedy assassinations. You know who really assassinated the Kennedys - Hitler. And Hitler really wasn't a Nazi. That was part of a cover-up by his real group, the Shriners. Those little cars they drive in, powered by cold fusion, they don't want anybody to know. It's a conspiracy."

"We should all search our papers for hidden messages, right?"

"They put hidden messages in the paper. That's how I found Diana wasn't really a princess. She was a Freemason, working for the Jesuits.  Ever wonder what those Masons keep in their jars?  Opium. That's how they control the world. The opium conspiracy. They put it in Slurpees to make them taste so good."

"Just thought you'd like to know. Chernobyl! You know what really happened? Aliens spilled a Slurpee on the control panel."

"Don't blame me after the New World Order takes over. They're going to force everyone to take opium and drink Slurpees. Want to know something really weird? Bin Laden and George Bush are brothers. "

*takes out a Slurpee from under his jacket*

"Wanna share my Slurpee...?"

"No? Guess some people just don't know how to handle the truth..."
